    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>FOREIGN BIDDERS FOR BRAZIL OIL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Petroleo Brasileiro SA, Brazil's national petroleum agency, says it authorized 44 companies from around the world, including the Exxon Mobil Corp and Texaco Inc, to bid on 23 new oil and gas exploration blocks as part of the government's effort to diversify country's petroleum industry (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brazil's national petroleum agency said it had authorized 44 companies from around the world, including the Exxon Mobil Corporation and Texaco Inc., to bid on 23 new oil and gas exploration blocks as part of the government's effort to diversify the country's petroleum industry. The blocks, which include 10 onshore and 13 offshore leases, will be sold at an auction on June 7. Brazil's oil and gas exploration was dominated by the state-owned oil company Petroleo Brasileiro S.A. until its monopoly ended in 1998.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
